"MAYDAY" and Thomas Barnett released <a1_0><b6_0>"Nude Photo"<b6_0/><a1_0/> in 1987 on May's label "<a2_0><b7_0>Transmat Records<b7_0/><a2_0/>", which helped kickstart the Detroit techno music scene and was put in heavy rotation on Chicago's Hot Mix 5 Radio DJ mix show and in many Chicago clubs.[citation needed] A year later, Transmat released what was to become one of techno and house music's classic anthems – the seminal track "Strings of Life".
